                            <comment id="14721416" author="githubbot" created="Sun, 30 Aug 2015 06:31:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user eginez opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/incubator-groovy/pull/105&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/incubator-groovy/pull/105&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-7519&quot; title=&quot;JsonOuput.toJson() leads to StackOverflowException&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-7519&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-7519&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Fixes JsonOuput.toJson() leads to StackOverflowException&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    JsonOutput overflows when serializing a File due to recursive references to File objects. Namely getAbsoluteFile(), getCanonicalFile(), and getParentFile(). These properties will be properly serialized by their counterpart methods getAbsolutePath(), getCanonicalPath() and getParent().&lt;/p&gt;

